## Auth Architecture

Dual-mode authentication â€” Clerk for web, JWT for mobile:

```
Request arrives
  â”śâ”€ Has Clerk session cookie?
  â”‚   â””â”€ Yes â†’ resolve via Clerk â†’ get internal user by clerkId
  â”śâ”€ Has Authorization: Bearer header?
  â”‚   â””â”€ Yes â†’ verify JWT (jose) â†’ get internal user by userId
  â””â”€ Neither?
      â””â”€ Return 401 via ApiError.unauthorised()
```

**Key files:**
- `src/lib/auth/get-auth.ts` â€” dual-mode resolver, single entry point
- `src/lib/auth/resolve-clerk-user.ts` â€” Clerk webhook â†’ local user upsert
- `src/lib/mobile-jwt.ts` â€” `signMobileJwt()` / `verifyMobileJwt()`
- `src/lib/auth-routing.ts` â€” public routes, auth routes, role-based access
- `src/middleware.ts` â€” Clerk middleware, protects non-public routes

**Webhook verification:** `svix` is pre-installed as a dependency. When you implement `src/app/api/webhooks/clerk/route.ts`, use `svix`'s `Webhook` class to verify the signature before processing the payload â€” never roll your own HMAC check. See [Clerk's svix integration guide](https://clerk.com/docs/integrations/webhooks/sync-data).

**Roles:** `admin`, `user` (defined in `src/types/index.ts`, stored on user record)

**Webhook sync:** Clerk fires `user.created` / `user.updated` / `user.deleted` â†’ `POST /api/webhooks/clerk` â†’ `resolveClerkUser()` upserts local record.

## Key Patterns

### API Route Handler

```typescript
// src/app/api/example/route.ts
import { getAuth } from '@/lib/auth/get-auth';
import { ok, created, handleError, ApiError } from '@/lib/api-response';
import { checkRateLimit, publicRateLimiter } from '@/lib/rate-limit';
import { getRequestContext } from '@/lib/request-context';
import { parsePagination } from '@/lib/validations';

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  try {
    const { ip } = await getRequestContext();
    const { success } = await checkRateLimit(ip, publicRateLimiter);
    if (!success) throw ApiError.rateLimited();

    const { page, pageSize } = parsePagination(request.nextUrl.searchParams);
    // ... query database ...
    return ok({ data: items, pagination: { page, pageSize, total, totalPages } });
  } catch (error) {
    return handleError(error);
  }
}
```

